St. Joseph 3, J.P. Stevens 2 (2OT): Mark Kim headed in a pass from Chris Taraska in the 95th minute to lead St. Joseph (3-6-1). Nick Cruz and Matt Pinho also scored. For J.P. Stevens (2-9), Jacob Hausman and Neil Gayam scored. Alex Corrigan tallied two assists. 
Scotch Plains-Fanwood 3, Union 0: Ari Rosenzweig, Stav Shadmi and Robert Viglione all scored for Scotch Plains-Fanwood (7-1-1). Patrick Ellman and Brian McManus each tallied an assist. 
North Brunswick 1, Piscataway 0: Kevin Weilson scored on an assist from Yardin Miranda to lead North Brunswick (3-8). Pawel Dzielski made six saves. Ried Couchie and Danny Saumett combined for 10 saves for Piscataway (0-11). 
Bernards 2, Somerville 0: Nico Arza and Connor O’Neill scored to lead Bernards (5-1-1). Dan Paez chipped in an assist. Will Sokol made three saves for Somerville (2-7). 
Watchung Hills 5, Phillipsburg 3: Tyler Pereira led Watchung Hills (4-2) with two goals and one assist. Keith Garcia recorded one goal and one assist. Matt Levin and Quinn Drigan also scored. Hans Hoffman tallied three assists. Read or Share this story: http://mycj.co/1KQ4SyK TOP VIDEOS
